{"title_page": "ICT University", "text_new": "{{Infobox university\n| name = ICT University\n| image = File:ICT university P Mbarika.jpg\n| image_upright = \n| motto = Imparting ICT in all academic disciplines\n| established = 2010\n| type = [[Higher education|Private University]] \n| president = [[Victor Mbarika]]\n| website = {{url|https://ictuniversity.org/}}\n\n}}\n\n'''ICT University''' is a [[Private university]] which operates a purely US-based [[curriculum]] with [[campuses]] in [[developing countries]] to provide [[ICT]] and Managerial Human Capacity [[Development]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ictuniversity.org/|title=ICT University \u2013 Imparting ICT in ALL Academic Disciplines|website=ictuniversity.org}}</ref>.\n\n==Background==\nICT [[University]] started in 2010 and it currently serves more than 15,000 students via on-site and online programs around the [[World]]. <br />The University develops productive and relevant Diploma, Bachelors, Masters and Doctoral level scholars to utilize their research and training in solving the substantial problems in their countries.\n\n==Programs and departments==\n*Bachelors of science in [[Natural science]]\n*Bachelors of science in [[accounting]]\n*Bachelors of science in [[ICT]]\n*Masters of Arts in Regional [[Development]] Planning\n*Masters of science in [[Applied statistics]]\n*Masters of science in [[Information and communication technology]]\n*Masters of science in Information systems and [[Computer network|networking]]\n*Masters of science in [[Public Health]]\n*Masters of science in [[Telecommunication]]\n*Masters in Business management and sustainable development\n*Masters in International [[Business Administration]]\n*PhD in [[Public Health]]\n*PhD in [[Business Administration]]\n*PhD in Business Administration for Sustainable Development \n*PhD in [[Software Engineering]]\n*PhD in Data Communication and Networking\n*PhD in [[Telecommunication]]\n*PhD in [[Information and Communication Technology]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ictuniversity.org/departments-and-programs/|title=Departments and Programs \u2013 ICT University|website=ictuniversity.org/departments-and-programs/}}</ref>\n\n==ICT University Foundation==\nThe ICT [[University]] [[Foundation (United States law)|Foundation]] is registered and chartered in the USA. It is the funding organ of all ICT University campuses. It also funds donations of ICT equipment, E-Learning laboratories and E-Libraries for many universities in developing nations in Africa<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thenationonlineng.net/u-s-varsity-donates-digital-library-enugu-college/|title=U.S. varsity donates digital library to Enugu college|date=October 18, 2017|website=Latest Nigeria News, Nigerian Newspapers, Politics}}</ref><ref> {{cite web | title=American varsity boosts e-learning with N90m ICT donation - Nigeria and World News | website=The Guardian Nigeria News - Nigeria and World News | date=2018-06-14 | url=https://guardian.ng/features/american-varsity-boosts-e-learning-with-n90m-ict-donation/ | access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>. The headquarter of African campuses is in Cameroon<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cameroonnewsagency.com/register-now-ict-university-2018-spring-semester/|title=Register NOW at ICT University For The 2018 Spring Semester}}</ref>. The University\u2019s Cameroon campus is accredited by Cameroon Ministry of Higher Education in 2012.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Universities in Cameroon|private}}\n\n\n{{coord missing|Nigeria}}\n\n[[Category:American University]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2010]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Cameroon]]\n[[Category:Universities in Cameroon]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Nigeria]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Africa]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox university\n| name = ICT University\n| image = File:ICT university P Mbarika.jpg\n| image_upright = \n| motto = Imparting ICT in all academic disciplines\n| established = 2010\n| type = [[Higher education|Private University]] \n| president = [[Victor Mbarika]]\n| website = {{url|https://ictuniversity.org/}}\n\n}}\n\n'''ICT University''' is a [[Private university]] which operates a purely US-based [[curriculum]] with [[campuses]] in [[developing countries]] to provide [[ICT]] and Managerial Human Capacity [[Development]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ictuniversity.org/|title=ICT University \u2013 Imparting ICT in ALL Academic Disciplines|website=ictuniversity.org}}</ref>.\n\n==Background==\nICT [[University]] started in 2010 and it currently serves more than 15,000 students via on-site and online programs around the [[World]]. <br />The University develops productive and relevant Diploma, Bachelors, Masters and Doctoral level scholars to utilize their research and training in solving the substantial problems in their countries.\n\n==Programs and departments==\n*Bachelors of science in [[Natural science]]\n*Bachelors of science in [[accounting]]\n*Bachelors of science in [[ICT]]\n*Masters of Arts in Regional [[Development]] Planning\n*Masters of science in [[Applied statistics]]\n*Masters of science in [[Information and communication technology]]\n*Masters of science in Information systems and [[networking]]\n*Masters of science in [[Public Health]]\n*Masters of science in [[Telecommunication]]\n*Masters in Business management and sustainable development\n*Masters in International [[Business Administration]]\n*PhD in [[Public Health]]\n*PhD in [[Business Administration]]\n*PhD in Business Administration for Sustainable Development \n*PhD in [[Software Engineering]]\n*PhD in Data Communication and Networking\n*PhD in [[Telecommunication]]\n*PhD in [[Information and Communication Technology]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ictuniversity.org/departments-and-programs/|title=Departments and Programs \u2013 ICT University|website=ictuniversity.org/departments-and-programs/}}</ref>\n\n==ICT University Foundation==\nThe ICT [[University]] [[Foundation (United S