-2019-naagin-bhagya-ka-zehrila-khel-becomes-no-1/2020/01/03|title=BARC India Ratings: Week 51 (2019); Naagin Bhagya Ka Zehrila Khel becomes no.1|accessdate=3 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\n\n====Season 1====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Episode\n! scope=\"col\" | Weekly rank<br />(in ratings)\n! scope=\"col\" | BARC ratings\n! scope=\"col\" | Television viewership<br />(in millions (TVM))<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.barcindia.co.in|title=Barc: this links to current day-select the date from drop down menu|work=Barc Ratings|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160113162833/http://www.barcindia.co.in/|archivedate=13 January 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" | Weekly rank<br />(in viewership)\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 1\n|1\n| 4.2\n| {{TableTBA|15676}}\n| {{TableTBA|1}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 2 & 3\n|1\n| 4.3\n| {{TableTBA|16741}}\n| {{TableTBA|1}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 4 & 5\n| 1\n| 4.5\n| {{TableTBA|N/A}}\n| {{TableTBA|1}}\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 6 & 7\n|1\n| 5.2\n| 16.71%\n| 1\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 8 & 9\n| 1\n| 5.7\n| 19.57%\n| 1\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 10 & 11\n| 1\n| 5.1\n| 17.81%\n| 1\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 12 & 13\n| 1\n| 5.3\n| 18.52%\n| 1\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 14 & 15\n| 1\n| 5.8\n| 18.54%\n| 1\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 16 & 17\n| 1\n| 5.8\n| 19.84%\n| 1\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 18 & 19\n| 1\n| 4.4\n| 19.82%\n| 1\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 20\n| 1\n| 5.3\n| 18.12%\n| 1\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 21 & 22\n| 1\n| 5.3\n| 17.11%\n| 1\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | 23 & 24\n| 1\n| 5.5\n| 19.54%\n| 1\n|}\n\n====Season 2====\nIn the table below, <span style=\"color:blue\">'''the blue numbers'''</span> represent the lowest ratings and <span style=\"color:red\">'''the red numbers'''</span> represent the highest ratings.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|- align=center\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Year / week\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Episodes\n!rowspan=\"2\"| Broadcast date\n!colspan=\"2\"| BARC